            "answer_text": "The article should be marked at Rs. 500.After allowing 10% discount, price will be Rs. 450.Profit = S. P. ( after discount) - C. P.=450-375=Rs.75 So the profit after allowing discount will be 75 Rs. Profit percentage = Profit\u00f7C. P \u00d7 100=75\u00f7375\u00d7 100=20%Your target profit is achieved! So to earn a profit of 20 % after giving discount of 10%, the price of the product must be Rs. 500. ",
